    "unit_type": "edited_selection",
    "label": "Extracts from the Account Rolls of the Abbey of Durham, Volume III",
    "scope_note": "Joseph Thomas Fowler's 1901 edited calendar and selection from Durham Cathedral Priory and Cathedral financial records, represented by the edition title page and printed pp. 577–743. It is not one medieval authored work, one manuscript, the complete surviving archive, or the complete Fowler volume. Historical records, separate physical copies and bills, Fowler's editorial compilation, the printed volume, the U-M encoding, and digital facsimiles remain distinct layers."
