  "notes": [
    "This record catalogs Fowler's edition-level selection because that is the coherent unit encoded by CME00048; medieval and post-Dissolution documentary creators are separated from Fowler's editorial responsibility.",
    "Latin is primary in the records, Middle English is embedded, and Fowler's substantial modern English editorial matter is separately recorded despite the XML's single enm declaration.",
    "All 233 exact public volume III-linked Durham IIIF objects are cached as complete provider-published inventories; physical coverage remains partial where only faces or otherwise incomplete surfaces are exposed.",
    "The manuscript images are not cleared for this project's commercial publishing workflow: exact manifests state CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 and Durham separately requires advance publication permission.",
    "The 2016 XML review records a later proofing and structural pass, not first publication or medieval creation."
